posts.raw_content:
My car is currently out of commission and I live on the edge of town far away from any grocery stores. As such, I'm at the mercy of getting a ride from someone or having food delivered.

Last night I made the mistake of placing an order from Walmart to be delivered this morning.  I waited up until the near end of the delivery window. I received notice that the order was on the way. I watched the tracker show the GPS location of the driver (named Jose Louis) and the guy overshot my street and was driving up and down another street.  

After about 5-10 minutes of this, I received notice that my order was delivered and it showed a picture of a house that was not mine and one that I did not recognize.  I walked outside and checked a few neighbors' porches to no avail. 

I reached out to Walmart and had to go through the motions with an AI chatbot just to get them to call me.  I received a call about 15 minutes later (AI again) before finally connecting to a human being.  Of course that  person was in India with a thick accent.  

She argued at first, saying my order was delivered and to the correct address. After a few minutes of that, I finally got her to refund my order. I still had to go in to the order to manually remove the tip because that was considered a separate charge that went directly to their (probably illegal) delivery driver.

So now I'm stuck without groceries. Fuck Walmart!
